---
import DocsNav from "../components/DocsNav.astro";
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import { evidence, repositoryUrl } from "../data/site";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Evidence — Loom Kernels"
  description="Hardware-qualified correctness and performance evidence for Loom Kernels on NVIDIA H20."
  active="Evidence"
>
  <header class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Evidence / NVIDIA H20</p>
    <h1>Claims with a measurement boundary.</h1>
    <p>
      Every reported latency names the shape, dtype, GPU, baseline, dispatcher,
      warm-up, sample count, and correctness gate. Microbenchmarks never stand in
      for model-level TTFT or TPOT.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="docs-layout">
    <DocsNav active="Evidence" />
    <article class="prose">
      <h2>Current qualified results</h2>
      <div class="evidence-grid">
        {evidence.map((item) => (
          <article class="evidence-card">
            <h3>{item.operator}</h3>
            <span class="result">{item.result}</span>
            <p>{item.detail}</p>
            <small>{item.shape}</small>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2>What the ratios mean</h2>
      <p>
        A ratio above 1.0 is baseline latency divided by Loom latency. For
        SiLU-and-Mul plus block FP8, the order-reversed CUDA Graph ratio of
        1.037–1.082 corresponds to 3.6–7.5% lower operator latency. Loom and the
        fused vLLM baseline had zero output-byte, scale, or dequantized mismatch.
      </p>

      <h2>Validation ladder</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Rust contract checks and CPU oracle.</li>
        <li>Raw CUDA correctness before event timing.</li>
        <li>PyTorch current-stream, mutation schema, and buffer-reuse tests.</li>
        <li><code>torch.compile</code> and CUDA Graph capture/replay.</li>
        <li>Named vLLM comparison with forward and reverse provider order.</li>
        <li>Real engine and end-to-end workload gates, tracked separately.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Reproduce</h2>
      <pre><code>PYTHONPATH=python/src \
python benchmarks/vllm_silu_and_mul_dynamic_fp8.py \
  --dtype bf16 --rows 8 --width 11008 --group-size 128 \
  --warmup 100 --iterations 2000 --samples 15 \
  --provider-order forward</code></pre>
      <p>
        Machine-readable reports are versioned in{" "}
        <a href={`${repositoryUrl}/tree/main/docs/results`}>docs/results</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
